parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, compromising the safety of the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
the airbag deploys unexpectedly
the airbag fails to deploy in an accident
the passenger airbag is bulging or lifting out of the dashboard
and the seatbelt light remains on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or unavailability of recall repairs can leave vehicles with defective airbags on the road, posing a risk to the safety of drivers and passengers.
symptoms: The part for the recall repair is not available
the manufacturer has exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair
and the dealer is unable to provide a timeline for the repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag sensor or dashboard can lead to inaccurate warnings or failures of the airbag system, compromising the safety of the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The airbag sensor is not working properly
the dashboard is damaged or malfunctioning
and the airbag warning light remains on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS HCU can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop
and a grinding sound is heard when braking over a bump.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A brake fluid leak can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaks onto the engine
smoke comes from underneath the hood
and the brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A delayed or failed brake response can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal takes a long time to respond
the brake pedal does not respond at all
and the vehicle is unable to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall repairs can cause owners to continue driving vehicles with known safety issues, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Owners receive recall notifications but are unable to schedule repairs due to parts unavailability
and dealerships are unable to provide a timeline for repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips in and out of gear
the vehicle jerks violently into pass gear
the transmission fails to shift
the vehicle loses power
and the check engine light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic throttle body can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
the check engine light is illuminated
the wrench light is illuminated
the vehicle goes into limp mode
and the vehicle stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coil can cause the vehicle to misfire, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine light is illuminated
the vehicle misfires
and the vehicle stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PTU can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
the check engine light is illuminated
and the vehicle stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the idler arm bolt can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The idler arm bolt breaks
and the vehicle loses power.
